--- !u!114 &321933907
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 321933906}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ea1c59ace054e0f4cb9e17e1e77a9b89, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueTrigger
  dialogueBox: {fileID: 1965924013}
  textComponent: {fileID: 1648123373}
  lines:
  - In this part of the world, the gods were old stories.
  - "The people who lived in the shadow of the great temples knew all the myths \u2014
    Ra who sailed his golden barque across the sky, Anubis who weighed the hearts
    of the dead, the old powers who had shaped the land long before anyone alive
    could remember."
  - 'Children grew up hearing these tales with wonder, and then with the comfortable
    distance of growing up. The temples were tourist sites now. '
  - The hieroglyphs were studied in universities. The gods were history.
  - Nobody truly expected them to be anything more.
  - Nesia's eyes opened to a sky the colour of hammered bronze.
  - "She came awake all at once \u2014 gasping, heart slamming, fingers clawing at
    the cracked earth beneath her as though she had been dropped from somewhere very
    far above. "
  - The air smelled of hot stone and something older, something electric, like the
    moment after lightning strikes.
  - "And then \u2014 before she could think, before she could even ask where she
    was \u2014 it came."
  - 'Not a voice, exactly. More like a pressure behind her eyes. A warmth in the
    centre of her chest. '
  textSpeed: 0.05
  playerTag: Player
  triggerOnce: 1
