--- !u!114 &1095423064
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1095423063}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ea1c59ace054e0f4cb9e17e1e77a9b89, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueTrigger
  dialogueBox: {fileID: 1832011199}
  textComponent: {fileID: 1672093819}
  lines:
  - 'And with it, muffled and distant, like a word spoken on the other side of a
    heavy door:'
  - '"...Rise."'
  - Then it was gone.
  - "Nesia sat in the dust, chest heaving. The word \u2014 if it had been a word
    \u2014 was already dissolving. She wasn't even certain she had heard anything
    at all. Perhaps her own mind had invented it, some last desperate signal firing
    in the moment between death and not-death."
  - Because she had been dead. She knew that the way you know things in your bones.
  - 'She looked down at her right hand. She was holding a pen. It was not an ordinary
    pen. Longer than it should have been, warm to the touch in the way that living
    things are warm. At its tip, a bead of deep gold ink trembled and caught the
    light. '
  - The pen hummed faintly against her palm. It did not feel like something she had
    found. It felt like something she had always carried.
  - (Where did this come from? Why does it feel like mine? It feels like it has always
    been mine.)
  - "Her past sat in her mind like a broken mosaic. Her name surfaced first: Nesia.
    Then fragments. A room full of books. The smell of ink. A deep and persistent
    hunger for knowing things \u2014 for reading and drawing and understanding how
    the world fitted together. And then \u2014 nothing."
  - "In the distance, half-swallowed by haze and time, a structure loomed \u2014
    massive, carved from sandstone the colour of dried blood. A temple. Even from
    here she could see the jackal-headed figures flanking its entrance."
  - The Anubis Temple.
  - (I know this place. Not from visiting it. From something else. From before.)
  - "The pen pulsed once in her hand \u2014 warm, steady, insistent \u2014 like a
    compass needle swinging to north."
  - Nesia looked at it. Looked at the temple. And walked.
  textSpeed: 0.05
  playerTag: Player
  triggerOnce: 1
